<refsect1 xml:id='description'><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
<para>A main window is a special kind of toplevel window used as the
outermost window in an application.</para>

<para>If <emphasis remap='I'>interp</emphasis> is associated with a Tk application then <function>Tk_MainWindow</function>
returns the application's main window. If there is no Tk application
associated with <emphasis remap='I'>interp</emphasis> then <function>Tk_MainWindow</function> returns NULL and
leaves an error message in <emphasis remap='I'>interp-&gt;result</emphasis>.</para>

<para><function>Tk_GetNumMainWindows</function> returns a count of the number of main
windows currently open in the process.</para>

</refsect1>

